{
  "texts": [
    "To compare the performance of these methods, we apply them to ANL-CE for training on CIFAR-10 under 0.8 symmetric noise.",
    "For simplicity and fair comparison, we use δ as the coefficient of the regularization term and consider it as an additional parameter of ANL.",
    "We keep α and β the same as in Section VI-D, tune δ for all three methods by following the parameter tuning setting in Appendix D-B.",
    "We also train networks without using any regularization method.",
    "The results are reported in Figure 5."
  ]
}